y%20at%20Dreamforce%2C%20Saleforce's%20annual%20technology%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESalesforce%20CEO%20Marc%20Benioff%20asked%20Pichai%20about%20what%20it%20was%20like%20for%20Google%2C%20which%20he%20described%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Babsolute%20leader%20in%20AI%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20time%2C%20when%20%26quot%3Bthis%20little%20company%20in%20San%20Francisco%20called%20OpenAI%20emerges%20with%20this%20product%20ChatGPT.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPichai%20said%20Google%20had%20already%20made%20significant%20progress%20on%20AI%20products%2C%20including%20an%20internal%20version%20of%20a%20chatbot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20you're%20right%2C%20credit%20to%20OpenAI%2C%20they%20put%20it%20out%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20OpenAI%20launched%20ChatGPT%20in%20late%202022%2C%20it%20had%20the%20backing%20of%20Microsoft%2C%20a%20rival%20of%20Google%2C%20and%20was%20largely%20seen%20as%20a%20major%20challenge%20to%20Google's%20dominance%20in%20the%20AI%20space.%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%20that%20management%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-management-issues-code-red-over-chatgpt-report-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20issued%20a%20%26quot%3Bcode%20red%26quot%3B%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Pichai%20redirected%20several%20teams%20to%20focus%20on%20AI%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20conversation%20with%20Benioff%2C%20Pichai%20compared%20the%20moment%20to%20others%20he%20had%20witnessed%20in%20the%20consumer%20internet%20space.%20For%20instance%2C%20when%20Google%20was%20working%20on%20video%20search%20in%202006%20and%20YouTube%20%26quot%3Bcame%20out%20of%20nowhere%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20when%20Facebook%20was%20seeing%20popularity%20with%20photos%20in%20its%20feed%2C%20and%20then%20Instagram%20appeared.%20(Google%20later%20bought%20YouTube%2C%20and%20Facebook%20bought%20Instagram.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20knew%20in%20a%20different%20world%2C%20we%20would've%20probably%20launched%20