li%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20former%20prosecutors%20still%20tell%20young%20lawyers%20to%20seek%20out%20government%20jobs.%20Others%20advise%20caution.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20a%20front-line%20federal%20prosecutor%20has%20long%20been%20a%20plum%20job.%20Across%20the%20US%2C%20hundreds%20of%20applications%20can%20be%20submitted%20for%20a%20single%20opening.%20While%20government%20service%20doesn't%20pay%20as%20much%20as%20some%20Big%20Law%20firms%2C%20the%20chance%20to%20deal%20with%20high-stakes%20investigations%2C%20trials%2C%20and%20legal%20arguments%20has%20long%20been%20a%20big%20draw%20for%20ambitious%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%20this%20year%2C%20however%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20has%20hired%20significantly%20fewer%20assistant%20US%20attorneys%20than%20in%20previous%20years%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20of%20data%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FWorkforce.AI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorkforce.AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20data%20analysis%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20January%20through%20August%2C%20about%2042%20people%20updated%20their%20LinkedIn%20pages%20to%20indicate%20that%20they%20had%20joined%20the%20Justice%20Department%20in%20such%20a%20role%2C%20which%20is%20down%20by%20more%20than%20half%20from%20the%20same%20period%20in%20each%20of%20the%20four%20preceding%20years%2C%20the%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterviews%20with%20current%20and%20former%20prosecutors%20suggest%20the%20hiring%20slowdown%20stems%20from%20a%20mixture%20of%20budget%20and%20political%20pressures.%20Hiring%20freezes%20have%20stalled%20recruitment%2C%20and%20pay%20raises%20have%20made%20bringing%20in%20new%20talent%20more%20expensive.%20The%20Department%20of%20Justice%20is%20also%20mired%20in%20turmoil%20under%20Trump%2C%20with%20sagging%20morale%20and%20potential%20recruits%20possibly%20worried%20about%20taking%20on%20ethically%20murky%20casework.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20came%20into%20this%20administration%2C%20we%20came%20in%20with%2030%25%20of%20vacancies%20in%20our%20criminal%20division%20already%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Brook%20Andrews%2C%20who%20recently%20joined%20the%20law%20firm%20Nelson%20Mullins%20from%20the%20US%20Attorney's%20Office%20in%20South%20Carolina%2C%20where%20he%20worked%20for%2010%20years%2C%20most%20recently%20as%20acting%20US%20attorney.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20staffing%20crisis%20in%20federal%20law%20enforcement%2C%20and%20if%20it's%20allowed%20to%20continue%2C%20it%20will%20make%20Americans%20less%20safe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20factors%2C%20like%20public%20skepticism%20of%20law%20enforcement%20and%20rising%20wages%2C%20have%20also%20played%20a%20role.%20One%20former%20senior%20Justice%20official%20who%20worked%20in%20the%20department%20during%20the%20Obama%20and%20Biden%20administrations%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20volume%20of%20applicants%20for%20AUSA%20spots%20fell%20significantly%20over%20his%20years%20at%20the%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20from%20the%20platform%20isn't%20comprehensive%20%E2%80%94%20some%20attorneys%20don't%20use%20LinkedIn%2C%20and%20others%20may%20be%20slow%20to%20update%20it%20with%20a%20new%20job.%20The%20decline%20is%20notable%20because%20these%20roles%20typically%20represent%20the%20lion's%20share%20of%20legal%20muscle%20in%20US%20attorneys'%20offices%20and%20because%20the%20Trump%20administration%20has%20called%20for%20increasing%20hiring%20of%20assistant%20US%20attorneys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20administration%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fmedia%2F1403736%2Fdl%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproposed%3C%2Fa%3E%20hiring%20more%20than%20400%20additional%20attorneys%20in%20the%20US%20Attorneys'%20Offices%2C%20bringing%20the%20total%20to%206%2C144.%20So%20far%2C%20that's%20off%20to%20a%20slow%20start.%20The%20hiring%20freeze%20that%20the%20president%20signed%20on%20his%20first%20day%20in%20office%20put%20a%20damper%20on%20some%20lawyer%20hiring%2C%20though%20it%20was%20later%20clarified%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-signs-executive-order-limiting-federal-hiring-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaw-enforcement%20roles%20like%20prosecutors%20were%20exempt%20from%20the%20freeze%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Elon%20Musk-led%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-department-of-government-efficiency%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%3C%2Fa%3E%20initiative%2C%20which%20was%20designed%20to%20slash%20the%20federal%20workforce%2C%20also%20spurred%20firings%20and%20retirements%20of%20some%20prosecutors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story%2C%20and%20people%20contacted%20at%20various%20US%20attorneys'%20offices%20didn't%20respond%20to%20questions%20about%20hiring.%20Auto-responses%20from%20some%20offices%20said%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgovernment-shutdown-what-to-know-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecurrent%20US%20government%20shutdown%3C%2Fa%3E%20prevented%20them%20from%20responding%20to%20media%20inquiries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Tessman%2C%20a%20former%20assistant%20US%20attorney%20in%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20West%20Virginia%2C%20said%20his%20office%20is%20down%20to%20about%2022%20attorneys%2C%20compared%20to%2037%20when%20it's%20fully%20staffed%2C%20with%2011%20departures%20in%202025.%20He%20said%20about%20five%20prosecutors%20took%20Musk's%20%26quot%3Bfork%2C%26quot%3B%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-federal-workers-employee-buyout-read-opm-letter-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeferred%20resignation%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20others%20left%20or%20resigned%20for%20other%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETessman%2C%20who%20was%20sent%20to%20Washington%20from%202022%20to%202025%20to%20work%20on%20January%206%20prosecutions%2C%20said%20he%20made%20plans%20to%20leave%20over%20the%20summer%20after%20Michael%20Gordon%2C%20a%20prosecutor%20in%20Florida%20who%20also%20worked%20on%20the%20cases%2C%20was%20summarily%20fired%20by%20Attorney%20General%20Pam%20Bondi.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fcapitol-riot-michael-gordon-prosecutor-fired-lawsuit-d7eac55266e6f63c096232d4b2a48b3e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGordon%20has%20sued%20over%20his%20termination%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20the%20case%20is%20pending%2C%20and%20the%20government%20hasn't%20yet%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20former%20colleagues%20still%20in%20government%2C%20Tessman%20said%2C%20have%20told%20him%20they%20are%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20trouble%20finding%20people%20who%20are%20qualified%20to%20do%20the%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20some%20of%20the%20nation's%2093%20US%20Attorneys'%20Offices%20are%20making%20a%20hiring%20push.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhiladelphia's%20US%20Attorney%20is%20hiring%2020%20frontline%20prosecutors%2C%20according%20to%20Bill%20McSwain%2C%20who%20led%20the%20office%20for%20part%20of%20the%20first%20Trump%20administration.%20The%20office%20covering%20Miami%20and%20southern%20Florida%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20said%20in%20job%20listings%20that%20it%20is%20hiring%20%26quot%3Bseveral%26quot%3B%20criminal%20prosecutors%20as%20well%20as%20civil%20and%20appellate%20assistant%20US%20attorneys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOJ%20doesn't%20appear%20to%20be%20lowering%20its%20standards%20to%20fill%20AUSA%20spots.%20Many%20of%20the%2042%20people%20who%20posted%20about%20taking%20new%20AUSA%20jobs%20worked%20for%20prominent%20law%20firms%20or%20state%20and%20local%20prosecutors'%20offices.%20More%20than%20a%20third%20went%20to%20a%20Top%2014%20law%20school%2C%20compared%20to%20under%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20roughly%20100%20people%20hired%20into%20AUSA%20roles%20four%20years%20ago%20who%20are%20still%20with%20the%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20has%20been%20at%20the%20center%20of%20several%20controversies%20during%20Trump's%20second%20term%2C%20including%20decisions%20to%20drop%20charges%20against%20the%20president's%20allies%2C%20like%20New%20York%20City%20Mayor%20Eric%20Adams%2C%20and%20investigate%20or%20charge%20adversaries%20like%20former%20prosecutor%20Jack%20Smith%2C%20New%20York%20Attorney%20General%20Letitia%20James%2C%20and%20former%20FBI%20Director%20James%20Comey%2C%20whose%20daughter%20was%20also%20fired%20from%20her%20job%20as%20a%20federal%20prosecutor%20without%20explanation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20department%20has%20also%20overseen%20the%20firings%20of%20dozens%20of%20prosecutors%20who%20investigated%20and%20charged%20people%20who%20sought%20to%20stop%20the%20certification%20of%20Joe%20Biden's%202020%20election%20victory%2C%20as%20well%20as%20senior%20antitrust%20and%20national-security%20prosecutors%20accused%20of%20disloyalty%20or%20misconduct%20by%20Trump's%20political%20allies.%20It%20has%20also%20faced%20accusations%20of%20a%20cover-up%20related%20to%20convicted%20sex%20offender%20Jeffrey%20Epstein.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20who%20led%20or%20worked%20in%20US%20Attorneys'%20Offices%20said%20new%20hires%20are%20unlikely%20to%20be%20involved%20in%20such%20controversies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20new%20federal%20prosecutors%20spend%20their%20first%20few%20years%20focusing%20on%20street%20crime%2C%20immigration%20violations%2C%20and%20sex%20offenses%2C%20regardless%20of%20which%20party%20sits%20in%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20margins%2C%20maybe%20there's%20a%20couple%20of%20ultra-liberal%20people%20who%20are%20like%2C%20'Oh%20well%2C%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20do%20that%20job%20because%20I%20don't%20like%20Donald%20Trump%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20McSwain.%20%26quot%3BFine.%20If%20some%20people%20are%20going%20to%20be%20like%20that%2C%20the%20people%20who%20do%20like%20the%20job%20are%20going%20to%20take%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20